%section.how-to#HowToConnect
  %h2 How To Connect
  %p
    That is pretty simple once the Sphero is ready (connected and listening), you just need three lines of code and you are set,
    Gobot and the Sphero driver take care of the rest.

    :markdown
      Install the library with: 
      `go get -u github.com/hybridgroup/gobot-sphero`

          :::go
          package main

          import (
            "github.com/hybridgroup/gobot"
            "github.com/hybridgroup/gobot-sphero"
          )

          func main() {

            spheroAdaptor := new(gobotSphero.SpheroAdaptor)
            spheroAdaptor.Name = "Sphero"
            spheroAdaptor.Port = "/dev/rfcomm0"

            sphero := gobotSphero.NewSphero(spheroAdaptor)
            sphero.Name = "Sphero"
          ...


%section.how-to#HowToUse
  %h2 How To Use
  %p 
    This example rolls the sphero in a random direction and change direction every 2 seconds.

    :markdown
          :::go
          package main

          import (
            "github.com/hybridgroup/gobot"
            "github.com/hybridgroup/gobot-sphero"
          )

          func main() {

            spheroAdaptor := new(gobotSphero.SpheroAdaptor)
            spheroAdaptor.Name = "Sphero"
            spheroAdaptor.Port = "/dev/rfcomm0"

            sphero := gobotSphero.NewSphero(spheroAdaptor)
            sphero.Name = "Sphero"

            work := func() {
              gobot.Every("2s", func() {
                sphero.Roll(100, uint16(gobot.Rand(360)))
              })
            }

            robot := gobot.Robot{
              Connections: []gobot.Connection{spheroAdaptor},
              Devices:     []gobot.Device{sphero},
              Work:        work,
            }

            robot.Start()
          }
          

